This article is an executive order issued by President Barack Obama on September 30, 2015. The order states that certain federal advisory committees will be continued or reestablished until September 30, 2017. The committees listed in the order cover a wide range of topics, including the preservation of the White House, national security, healthcare, education, and environmental issues. The functions of the President under the Federal Advisory Committee Act will be performed by the head of the department or agency designated after each committee. This order supersedes a previous executive order from 2013 and amends an executive order from 1993. The order is effective as of September 30, 2015.